titleInfo.title: Program from Annual Banquet, Tennessee Chapter, American Institute of Architects, 1923 October 3. Inside.

location.physicalLocation: Special Collections Division of the Nashville Public Library, 615 Church Street, Nashville, Tennessee, 37219

mods.abstract: This program from the 1923 Annual Banquet of the Tennessee Chapter of the American Institute of Architects, held at the Centennial Club, boasts a number of distinguished guests, including architect and past president Henry C. Hibbs. Henry C. Hibbs was elected as a member of the American Institute of Architects in March 1919. From 1919 to 1920, he served as a sponsor, charter member and first president of the Tennessee Chapter of the A.I.A. Forms part of the Henry C. Hibbs Papers. 1 program : col. ; 5.25 in. x 9.5 in.
